Description This frame is specific to visiual perception of some entity or situation

Maps to IARPA Source Concept(s)
Other aliases Vision
Comments The LU 'see' may be problematic for extraction

Unlike FrameNet's 'Perception_experience' frame, this frame is specific to vision. Parameters that affect the See-er's ability to see an object include: - light conditions around seen_object - degree of obstruction - visual acuity of See-er - distance between See-er and Seen_object - perspective from which See-er sees seen_object - visually-accessible parts of the Object_seen - See-er’s visual area (focal area, and overall field of vision) - distance between See-er and seen_object
